---
description: Testing conventions
globs: **/*.test.ts, e2e/**
---

- Unit test (Vitest): services and non-trivial lib utilities. Test behavior and
  edge cases, not implementation details. Skip trivial UI snapshot tests.
- E2E (Playwright): only the critical flows — signup/login, checkout/billing,
  and each feature's primary happy path (its spec lists which).
- Tests are independent: no shared mutable state, no execution-order dependence.
  Each e2e test creates its own user/org via the seed helpers.
- Use factories in tests/factories.ts for test data — no hand-rolled objects
  repeated across files.
- A task is not complete while tests are red. Never weaken or delete a failing
  test to make it pass — fix the code or flag the spec conflict.
